​1. Introduction
​The Portfolio of Evidence (PoE) for this Web Development module is a comprehensive, practical summation designed to evaluate our capability to build a secure, fully functional, relational database-driven web application. The core objective of this project was to move away from third-party frameworks and instead engineer a complete e-commerce ecosystem using vanilla PHP, native HTML5/CSS3, and structural SQL queries through MySQLi.
​My understanding of this PoE is that it simulates a live production environment where data integrity, relational mapping, and user role separation are paramount. We chose to build PASTIMES, a second-hand clothing marketplace tailored for the South African market. This application addresses a complex technical problem: managing three entirely separate user journeys (Buyers, Sellers, and Administrators) that all read and write to a single, highly normalized database. The PoE pushed us to look past simple presentation layers and deeply understand state management, transactional logic, data validation, and secure server-side tracking, serving as an exceptional benchmark for our growth as software developers.


