3. Research, Technology, and the Presentation of Information
​Scenario 1: Developing Secure multi-tier Image Upload and Validation Systems
​One of the most technically demanding tasks I had to research was building a secure file upload pipeline for the clothing listing form. Because letting public users upload files to a server presents severe security risks, I had to thoroughly research PHP’s native global $_FILES array and file handling mechanisms.
​I researched how to securely validate incoming files beyond their surface extensions. I investigated how to verify MIME types using the finfo class to ensure that an uploaded file was genuinely a valid image format (JPG, PNG, or WebP) and not an executable script disguised as an image. I also researched how to implement size restrictions and automatically generate unique file names using functions like uniqid() to prevent users from accidentally overwriting existing product images on the server root. This research allowed me to build a clean, secure image upload engine that seamlessly saves files into the images/products/ directory while recording the correct path string in tblClothing.
​Scenario 2: Managing Relational Data Integrity during Checkout Transactions
​Another critical research scenario involved managing complex relational data state shifts when a buyer completes a purchase. I had to research how to write optimized, secure SQL operations that safely modify multiple tables simultaneously without creating data discrepancies.
​I analyzed how to execute data insertions into tblOrder using foreign keys that mapped directly back to userID from tblUser and clothingID from tblClothing. I had to ensure that when a purchase was finalized, the specific item's status column inside tblClothing was immediately updated to 'Sold' via an automated database update string. This research was essential to avoid race conditions—such as two buyers trying to purchase the exact same unique piece of clothing at the same time—ensuring a smooth, reliable transaction presentation that successfully met the strict criteria of the PoE guidelines.
